settings.heading: Technical Specifications
settings.content:
Engineered for safe, effective, and easy home-based mild hyperbaric oxygen therapy (mHBOT), this horizontal lying chamber delivers consistent pressure up to 1.5 ATA. It is ideal for athletes and anyone seeking improved recovery, energy, and mental focus.

The all-in-one system ensures smooth pressure regulation and reliable oxygen delivery with an integrated oxygen concentrator (5 L/min) and a powerful air compressor (55 L/min), providing a comfortable and consistent therapy experience every session.Pressure: 1.3 ATA / 1.4 ATA / 1.5 ATA

  • Material: Thermoplastic Polyurethane (TPU)
  • Dimensions (Inflated): 94.5" L × 32.5" W × 32.5" H (±2")
  • Dimensions (Uninflated): 88.5" L × 31.5" W × 31.5" H
  • Weight: 29 lbs
  • Air Compressor: 16" L × 10" W × 11" H
  • Type: Quiet, oil-free; activated carbon filters at air inlet and outlet
  • Air Cooler: 7.2" L × 5" W × 14" H
  • Description: Provides cooling and dehumidification to enhance comfort
  • Oxygen Concentrator: 14" L × 13" W × 23" H
  • Flow Rate: 5 L/min or 10 L/min
  • Technology: PSA molecular sieve; continuous oxygen production (no tank)

settings.heading: The Warrior Willpower Mission
settings.description:
Our mission is simple: to make advanced recovery accessible, not limited to elites or medical clinics. We build hyperbaric recovery equipment designed for real, everyday use at home, without compromising on quality or convenience.

We focus on performance, reliability, and features that actually matter to athletes and active individuals. No inflated markups. No gimmicks. Just dependable recovery equipment built to support long-term performance and wellness.

settings.text: After being diagnosed with aggressive small cell carcinoma in my liver, I was given a very difficult prognosis. During treatment, I decided to incorporate an oxygen chamber at home alongside my medical care. It was a challenging journey, but over time I noticed improvements in my strength and overall well-being. Today, almost four years later, there has been no sign of recurrence, and even my oncologist has called my recovery remarkable. I truly believe oxygen therapy played an important supportive role in helping me stay strong through one of the toughest periods of my life.

After having several teeth removed following radiation therapy for neck cancer, my gums struggled to heal and I was concerned about long-term complications. I started oxygen therapy and after about 20 sessions I noticed steady improvement — my gums began healing and I felt generally better overall. Even my follow-up appointments showed encouraging progress. I’m grateful I added this therapy to support my recovery.

I started using an oxygen chamber as part of my wellness routine in my early 40s, hoping to improve energy and recovery. After a few months of regular sessions, I noticed deeper sleep, clearer focus, faster workout recovery, and healthier-looking skin. It’s now a core part of how I take care of myself and maintain my day-to-day energy.

While preparing for an important surgery, my doctor recommended oxygen therapy before and after the procedure. I decided to invest in a chamber for home use and stayed consistent with treatments. My recovery felt smoother than expected, and I was able to regain strength steadily. I’m thankful I had this extra support during such an important time.

I was dealing with a shoulder injury just weeks before a major competition and was looking for ways to support recovery. Adding oxygen therapy to my routine made a noticeable difference — I felt better prepared physically and mentally going into the event. Since then, it’s remained a regular part of my training and recovery plan.

After incorporating oxygen therapy into my recovery plan, I noticed steady progress and felt supported throughout the healing process. My recovery went more smoothly than expected, and even my doctor commented on how well I was progressing. I believe the chamber played an important role in helping me get back to feeling like myself.

settings.heading: What does a hyperbaric chamber do?
settings.row_content: It delivers oxygen at higher-than-normal pressure, helping the body absorb more oxygen and support recovery, healing, and overall wellness.

settings.heading: Who can use a hyperbaric chamber?
settings.row_content: Athletes, people recovering from injuries, individuals managing fatigue, and those focused on general wellness often use it. Usage should always follow professional guidance.

settings.heading: How long is a typical session?
settings.row_content: Most sessions last between 60 to 90 minutes, depending on the protocol and goals.

settings.heading: Is hyperbaric therapy safe?
settings.row_content: When used correctly and under recommended guidelines, hyperbaric chambers are considered safe. Proper training and adherence to safety instructions are essential.

settings.heading: How often should hyperbaric therapy be used?
settings.row_content: Frequency depends on individual goals. Some users opt for a few sessions per week, while others use it as part of a structured recovery plan.

settings.title: Hyperbaric oxygen chamber
settings.text: Unfold the chamber on a flat surface and fully extend it. Once connected, it inflates and holds pressure automatically during your session.

settings.title: Oxygen concentrator
settings.text: Place the concentrator next to the chamber and connect it using the provided tubing. It supplies a steady flow of oxygen throughout your session.

settings.title: Air compressor
settings.text: Position the compressor near the chamber and attach it to the air inlet. It inflates the chamber and maintains the required pressure.

settings.title: Oxygen mask and tubing
settings.text: Connect the tubing from the oxygen concentrator to the mask. Wear the mask comfortably inside the chamber to receive oxygen during use.

settings.title: Filters and connectors
